article.headline: Wright St. 76, Ill.-Chicago 75
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Vaughn Duggins scored a team-high 19 points to help Wright State hold on for a 76-75 win over Illinois-Chicago on Thursday night. Todd Brown's 3-pointer with 12 seconds left built an insurmountable 76-72 lead for Wright State (10-6, 3-4 Horizon League). Jordan Pleiman scored 12 points and Scottie Wilson added 10 points for the Raiders. Wright State, which led 39-38 at the half, went ahead for good on a layup by Duggins with 54 seconds left. That, along with Brown's shot, were enough so Josh Mayo's last-second 3-pointer couldn't lift Illinois-Chicago (9-8, 3-3) to the win. Troy Tabler's 3-pointer extended the Raiders' lead to 11 points with 13:59 left. But the Flames climbed back in the game on 48 percent second-half shooting. Mayo led Illinois-Chicago with 21 points. Karl White Jr. scored 20 points and Tori Boyd chipped in 11.
